Creating the three new columns 'Monetary' , 'Recency' , 'Frequency'

In [24]:
#Getting the overall price for each order by multiplying unit price of the order with quantity 
df4['Monetary'] = df4['Quantity'] * df4['UnitPrice']
In [25]:
#Getting only the date out of the overall Invoice date column containing Time +Date 
df4['Date'] =  pd.to_datetime(df4['InvoiceDate']).dt.date
df4['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df4['Date'])
In [26]:
# Defining a new Analysis date for finding the Recency
df4['AnalysisDate'] = pd.to_datetime('2011-12-09')
In [27]:
df4['dif'] = df4['AnalysisDate'] - df4['Date'] #Finding the difference for each date column
df4['dif'] = df4['dif'].astype(str) # Converting the date type to string to only take the numeric portion out of the format
df4['Recency'] = df4.dif.str.extract('(\d+)')#Extracting only the numeric portion from the subracted date column
df4['Recency'] = df4['Recency'].astype(int) # Finally getting the recency column for each invoice
In [28]:
df5 = df4.groupby(by = ['CustomerID']).min() #Getting the minimum recency number for each customer as that is the genuine recency

Removal of outliers from the 3 features using the Inter Quartile approach

Removing outliers from Recency column

In [36]:
Q1_Recency = np.percentile(df7['Recency'] ,25 ) #Fetching the 25th percentile of data 
Q3_Recency = np.percentile (df7['Recency'], 75) # Fetching the 75th percentile of data 
IQR_Recency = Q3_Recency - Q1_Recency # Fetching the IQR 
print (Q1_Recency, Q3_Recency , IQR_Recency)
upper_limit_Recency = Q3_Recency + 1.5 * IQR_Recency
lower_limit_Recency = Q1_Recency - 1.5 *IQR_Recency
print (upper_limit_Recency , lower_limit_Recency)

outliers_Recency = {}
for i in range (0 , len(df7['Recency'])):
    if df7['Recency'].iloc[i]>upper_limit_Recency:
        outliers_Recency[i] = df7['Recency'].iloc[i]
        df7['Recency'].iloc[i] = upper_limit_Recency
    elif df7['Recency'].iloc[i]<lower_limit_Recency:
        outliers_Recency[i] = df7['Recency'].iloc[i]
        df7['Recency'].iloc[i] = lower_limit_Recency
# print(outliers_Recency)

Plotting the distortion score for different k values from 1-10

In [41]:
# Training the model on K-means clustering 
from sklearn.cluster import KMeans
elbow = {}
for i in range(1,11):
    km = KMeans(n_clusters= i)
    km.fit(df7)
    elbow[i] =km.inertia_ #Storing the distortion score for each K- Value in the dictionary with the key as the k values 
# and the value as the distortion score for each K- Value
elbow #Printing out the dictionary
